&quot;Sunday 20th: Dark day snowed a little. Left Welshes shanty about 1/2 past 3 O'clock with A. Lebo and walked to Murphys shty. Staid overnight.&quot;

&quot;Mo 21: Dark day snowed some. Staid at Murphys all day posting books. Murphy building blacksmith shop.&quot;

&quot;Tuesday 22nd: Dark cloudy day snowed some but quite warm. Left Murphy shanty about 12 O'clock. Walked to Welshes with Tim Murphy. A. Teabo [Thibeault?] and Tim Murphy left there about 1/2 pas 1 with Welshes men &amp; Welsh. Rode with Wm Diamon to Queensboro. Had supper and fed mules &amp; went to Tweed that night. Staid over night at E. Gabouries. Maloney &amp; Johnston faught in yard.&quot;

&quot;Wednesday 23rd: Cloudy in the morning and snowed verry heavy left Tweed about 7 OClock rode to Roslin with Diamond. Met P. Murphy with team. Left there about 10 OClock &amp; got Home at 1/4 past 12. J. Doyle &amp; L. Murphy staid for dinner. Bright after noon.&quot;

&quot;Thursday 24th: Fine Day. Rode to Lonsdale with P. Murphy after his sleigh. He drove the colts. Bought boots for Jane &amp; Groceries &amp;c Met Time going to mill with grist when coming home at Whitemans.&quot;

Part of Denis Nealon's diary.
